  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "These artefacts arise due to the rendering differences between peripheral and non-peripheral areas, regardless of the degradation technique employed.",
    "Furthermore, the peripheral areas are especially sensitive to contrast changes, even more than stereoscopic depth.",
    "Studies combating this problem, for instance by blurring the limits between distinct areas, have not yet completely solved it since they also modify the image contrast (Mohanto et al. 2022).",
    "As occurred in eye-tracking, rendering can also be helped by machine learning, although it is still in an early stage which makes these solutions not robust enough for their commercialization.",
    "Nevertheless, previous work has already achieved the completion of images using GAN networks (Kaplanyan et al. 2019)."
  ],
